A5DC0E5", "musicInfo": {"artist_name": "altego_music", "song_name": "DROP IT LIKE ITS HOT x STAYIN ALIVE (ALT\u00c9GO MIX)", "uses_original_audio": true, "should_mute_audio": false, "should_mute_audio_reason": "", "audio_id": "35471216759159857"}, "ownerUsername": "cleanmama", "ownerFullName": "Clean Mama\u00ae", "transcript": "When the pimps in the crib, ma, drop it like it's hot."}, {"shortCode": "DagvLIJtb5j", "url": "https://www.instagram.com/p/DagvLIJtb5j/", "caption": "Paper clutter isn\u2019t usually about too much mail. It\u2019s about too many decisions.\n\nEvery envelope asks a question:\n\u2022 Do I need this?\u2028\u2022 Should I pay it?\u2028\u2022 Should I keep it?\u2028\u2022 Where does it go?\n\nWhen there isn\u2019t a simple answer, paper ends up on the counter \u201cfor later.\u201d\n\nI don\u2019t think of this as organizing\u2014it\u2019s a system.\n\nEvery piece of mail gets one decision:\u2028\ud83d\udcec Recycle\u2028\ud83d\udcc2 Action\u2028\ud83d\uddc3\ufe0f File\n\nOnce those decisions are made, the clutter never has a chance to build.\n\nSmall systems like this are what make a home feel calmer. They don\u2019t eliminate tasks\u2014they eliminate the constant mental load of wondering what to do next.\n\nWhat\u2019s one area of your home that needs a better system instead of more organizing?\n\n\u2714\ufe0fComment HOURS and I\u2019ll send you 10\nsystems that Save Me Hours Every Week and a couple other resources to help you get started!", "timestamp": "2026-07-08T00:18:59.000Z", "videoDuration": 14.2, "videoPlayCount": 18260, "videoViewCount": 4262, "likesCount": 98, "commentsCount": 13, "displayUrl": "https://instagram.fagc1-2.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t51.82787-15/734367491_18606695755038124_2024934335623792336_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e15_tt6&_nc_ht=instagram.fagc1-2.fna.fbcdn.net&_nc_cat=104&_nc_oc=Q6cZ2gE4F_GYh1VFQRy1k26BffzXWBfThPFnEcqDMJZPQwjHGrRmaObP-Mq-j-gM-CigTcQ&_nc_ohc=4no1SMid7gAQ7kNvwExpEQ1&_nc_gid=gU60X3XgM06iLnVBux-EnA&edm=ADp7STQBAAAA&ccb=7-